from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error, mean_absolute_error
In [39]:
def model_train_test_covid(Model):
    model = Model()
    model.fit(in_train, out_train)
    train_pred = model.predict(in_train)
    test_pred = model.predict(in_test)
    train_mse = mean_squared_error(train_pred, out_train)
    train_mae = mean_absolute_error(train_pred, out_train)
    test_mse = mean_absolute_error(test_pred, out_test)
    test_mae = mean_absolute_error(test_pred, out_test)
    return(train_mse,train_mae,test_mse,test_mae)
